raw_data.title: User Experience Strategy Lead
raw_data.description: Serves as the overall Mediabarn team lead, providing the vision for the planning and delivery of all CX and UX research and design initiatives provided by the team. Provides strategic planning and management consulting and assists federal leads with design strategy and stakeholder management, including workshops, meetings and cross-team communication. Helps evangelize experience research and design methods to various stakeholders who may not yet be experienced in this area. Facilitates ideation sessions to identify solutions that target specific audiences and help meet business objectives. Supports efforts for understanding resource demands for project initiatives including prioritization and planning. Ensures deliverables are of the highest quality and are delivered within time and budget parameters. Assists federal leads with team coordination, scheduling and communication, and serves as their main POC for the engagement. Note, industry terms ‘customer experience’ (CX), 'user experience' (UX), 'human-centered design' (HCD) and 'user-centered design' (UCD) are sometimes used interchangeably.

raw_data.title: User Experience Researcher
raw_data.description: Assesses the current user experience and seeks to understand future user experience needs. Plans, moderates, and summarizes reporting of a wide range of research activities. Provides strategic planning and management consulting. Coordinates with the design team to ensure design assets are in alignment with the goals of the studies being conducted. Conducts and evaluates qualitative and quantitative research to understand needs, goals, and challenges to make recommendations for maximum project benefit. Conducts data collection and analysis through ethnographic, in-depth interviews (IDIs), focus groups, usability testing, surveys, persona creation, and experience mapping research activities. Develops personas for various audience segments to enable a common understanding of customer needs, motivations and pain points. Identifies, portrays, and evaluates the existing as well as to-be-created journey for a particular persona to help understand users and their challenges. Oversees research lab operations including participant recruitment and scheduling, incentive disbursement, facility and equipment set-up, and recording of research sessions. Note, industry terms ‘customer experience’ (CX), 'user experience' (UX), 'human-centered design' (HCD) and 'user-centered design' (UCD) are sometimes used interchangeably.

raw_data.title: Senior User Experience Designer
raw_data.description: Serves in experience design and design prototyping roles. Provides strategic planning and management consulting as well as design deliverables which can include but are not limited to information structure (IA), navigation, user flows, product workflows, wireframes, customer/user journeys, storyboards that illustrate the customer experience, user interface elements, and interaction models. Creates design elements including visual design concepts and explorations, style tiles/mood boards, pattern libraries, style guides, iconography, clickable design prototypes for usability testing and stakeholder review purposes, design systems, specifications and as well as other design assets as appropriate. Provides design deliverables to product development teams for implementation. Provides guidance and direction to other practitioners. Note, industry terms ‘customer experience’ (CX), 'user experience' (UX), 'human-centered design' (HCD) and 'user-centered design' (UCD) are sometimes used interchangeably.
